race.comment: PULL MY FINGER (3) has placed in both runs to date and looks to have found an ideal race here. His debut over this route was good when beaten under a length before an even effort out to 1112m at Kilmore, finishing third but well behind a runaway winner. Back to 1000m suits and this looks winnable on exposed form. FARAWAY DREAM (8) is a filly by Farnan on debut for the Busuttin & Young stable. She's won a jumpout leading in and should prove very competitive first time out. SCUSIES (10) was much better dropping back to this trip second up at Echuca. Gets a significant jockey change here and can prove hard to hold out. SHE'S OURVALENTINE (11) was just fair on debut at Cranbourne but should be better for it.
